HEADWORD: Wayfaring
<hw>Way"far`ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Traveling; passing; being on a
journey.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>wayfaring</xex> man.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Judg.
xix. 17.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Wayfaring tree</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a
European shrub (<spn>Viburnum lantana</spn>) having large ovate leaves
and dense cymes of small white flowers.</cd> -- <col><b>American
wayfaring tree</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the (<spn>Viburnum
lantanoides</spn>).</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

